[Macaulay2.com](https://macaulay2.com/) also known as M2, is a computer algebra software designed for research in algebraic geometry and commutative algebra. Its built-in algebraic objects make it especially convenient for exploring polynomial rings. The development is community-based, the code is open source, and the functionalities are continuously improved.

One barrier to access is the installation that, given the sophistication of the software, requires terminal use and some homebrew knowledge. In an effort to onboard undergraduates quickly to Macaulay2, I have been involved in the [GitHub for Mathematicians](https://g4m.code4math.org/) project to learn and document workflows that require minimal specialized coding knowledge. 

